text: Baranyntsi (Ukrainian: Баранинці; Hungarian: Baranya) is a village in the Uzhhorodskyi Raion in the Zakarpattia Oblast in western Ukraine. Baranya is 3 km south-southeast of Uzhhorod. == History == It was settled at the beginning of the 14th century. Its first written mention dates back to 1342 under the name Barania. The origin of its name is unclear. == References == Category:Settlements of Uzhhorod District Category:Villages in Ukraine
